President Trump has signed into law the Rodchenkov Act, which aims to combat doping in international sporting events. The act includes robust penalties for individuals and entities involved in unfair competition. The Office of National Drug Control Policy (ONDCP) Director, Jim Carroll, expressed the United States' commitment to strengthening fair sport globally. The Rodchenkov Act received unanimous bipartisan support in the House and Senate. The ONDCP thanked domestic and international partners, including the U.S. Helsinki Commission, the U.S. Anti-Doping Agency, Global Athlete, and FairSport, for their support. The act aims to hold accountable those who participate in international doping fraud conspiracies and emphasizes the importance of legal consequences for enabling unfair competition.